column33: Movie goers and supporters of Johnny Depp: Remove Amber Heard and Robbie Margot from Pirates of the Carribean fran chise
column34:
A franchise to be successful has to be given great character indepth. Johnny Depp has given great justice and character to Capt Jack Sparrow -the franchise of the Pirates of the Carribean is nothing without Capt Jack Sparrow. 

No harm with putting strong women characters as this has been the legacy of the franchise, but to reboot and remove the main protagonist by replacing them with an all-woman cast, and with Amber Heard no doubt, is adding insult to injury to a growing cult classic. She has sullief already JD's legacy in Hollywood-to further kill the iconic characters that he has helped build is overkill in her mission to ruin JD. 

Do not kill off the franchise by putting her in it-as well as with any actor supporting Amber Heard

column2:
I’m going to say the same things I’ve said everywhere else.

I think they both hit each other and each should take responsibility for how they hurt each other but I think Johnny Depp still deserves to have his career back. 
It’s not fair that she still has hers but he can’t play roles at all. He should be allowed to have his roles back if they both struck or hurt each other and she has her career but he doesn’t have his. I don’t think it’s fair either way to take one persons career away or the other’s while one person keeps theirs if they both hit each other and did the same things. Either make both of their careers suffer for that or just let Johnny have his career back. Im more for the latter of just allowing him have his career back.

column2: Johnny Depp is clearly innocent. Amber Heard is the guilty one based on the evidence. I am standing behind Johnny Depp on this matter. Moving forward, my family and I will not support any film, show, or product that Amber Heard is apart of. Nor will I support any films, shows, or products that Johnny Depp would have been apart of if it wasn't for Ambers lies. I was looking forward to upcoming movies like Fantastic Beasts 3, Aquaman 2, and a new Pirates of the Caribbean, but no longer, and I will not support them unless changes are made. Extremely disappointed with the decisions that's been made.
